HEADWORD: Hylodes
<hw>Hy*lo"des</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/ woody, wooded, muddy; <?/ a wood + <grk>e'i^dos</grk> form.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The piping frog (<spn>Hyla Pickeringii</spn>), a
small American tree frog, which in early spring, while breeding in
swamps and ditches, sings with high, shrill, but musical,
notes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

